Irène Schweizer (born 2 June 1941) is a Swiss jazz and free improvising pianist.
With Yusef Lateef, Uli Trepte and Mani Neumeier, she performed at the Montreux Jazz Festival in 1967.
One of her most enduring collaborations is with the improvising musician Rüdiger Carl.
